<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - TROUBLESHOOTING - EXTERNAL LEAKAGE AT HYDRO-MAX&#8482;
        BOOSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXTERNAL LEAKAGE AT HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BOOSTER</title>
        <table id="t0401704" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="s1t3"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CONDITION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">POSSIBLE CAUSE</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CORRECTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="5">
                            <para>External power steering fluid leak, Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Leaks at inlet line fitting nut of Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Replace inlet line fitting O-ring. Tighten fitting nut. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Leaks at interface between Hydro-Max&#8482; booster housing and booster backup
                                pump.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Replace seals, make sure seal grooves are clean, tighten mounting bolts. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>. If
                                backup pump seal surface damaged, replace backup pump.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Leak at flow switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace flow switch O-ring, tighten flow switch. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Leak at outlet hose connection to Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Tighten hose clamp. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>. If hose
                                damaged, replace it. If booster outlet port nipple damaged, replace booster.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Leaks at any other location on Hydro-Max&#8482; booster (not including backup
                                pump).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5. Replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster. (Do not replace backup pump.)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Leaks at any other location on backup pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6. Replace backup pump. (Do not replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="s1t3">
                            <note>
                                <para>To determine if leakage is from the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster or the master
                                    cylinder, mix leaked fluid with water. Brake fluid from the master cylinder will mix
                                    with water. Power steering fluid from the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster will not mix with
                                    water.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
